        "min": 0.1,
        "max": 1000,
        "unit": "ns",
        "value": 20,
        "description": "Nanosecond regime preferred for cost-effective cleaning of PTFE; picosecond (ps) or femtosecond reduces heat-affected zone (HAZ <10 μm) but increases cost; 20 ns minimizes thermal damage due to PTFE's poor conductivity. Avoid fs for industrial scale. Source: Laser physics research in Applied Surface Science (2019) on polymer ablation thresholds."
